### ===========================
### Schedule API Tests
### Includes happy-path + security/constraint violation scenarios
### ===========================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api/schedule
@accessToken = {{login.response.body.accessToken}}
@memberId = 7a3a3f00-6830-4037-a818-b3525899131c
@membershipId = fdb2da27-a80b-4de8-9787-b92d3f598cbb


### -----------------------------------------------
### Login (prerequisite for accessToken)
### -----------------------------------------------
# @name login
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "user@example.com",
    "password": "Password456!"
}


### ===========================
### HAPPY PATH
### ===========================

### 1. Create Schedule (SCHEDULED)
# @name createSchedule
POST {{baseUrl}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "memberId": "{{memberId}}",
    "membershipId": "{{membershipId}}",
    "scheduledAt": "2026-04-20T10:00:00.000Z",
    "sessionDuration": 60,
    "status": "SCHEDULED"
}

### 2. Create Schedule directly as ATTENDED
### → Triggers remainingSessions decrement + RevenueRecognition creation
POST {{baseUrl}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "memberId": "{{memberId}}",
    "membershipId": "{{membershipId}}",
    "scheduledAt": "2026-04-21T10:00:00.000Z",
    "sessionDuration": 60,
    "status": "ATTENDED"
}

### 3. Get All Schedules
GET {{baseUrl}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 4. Get Schedules filtered by member
GET {{baseUrl}}?member-id={{memberId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 5. Get Schedule by ID
@scheduleId = {{createSchedule.response.body.id}}

GET {{baseUrl}}/{{scheduleId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}


### ===========================
### STATE TRANSITIONS (Idempotency Tests)
### ===========================

### 6. Reschedule (SCHEDULED → SCHEDULED, time change only)
### → No financial side effect
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{scheduleId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "scheduledAt": "2026-04-20T14:00:00.000Z",
    "sessionDuration": 60
}

### 7. Check-in (SCHEDULED → ATTENDED)
### → Decrement remainingSessions + create RevenueRecognition
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{scheduleId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "status": "ATTENDED"
}

### 8. Idempotency check: PATCH unrelated field while ATTENDED
### → Expected: NO duplicate revenue record created
###   (wasAttended && willBeAttended → no-op on side effects)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{scheduleId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "scheduledAt": "2026-04-20T15:00:00.000Z"
}

### 9. Revert to SCHEDULED (ATTENDED → SCHEDULED)
### → Increment remainingSessions + delete RevenueRecognition
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{scheduleId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "status": "SCHEDULED"
}

### 10. Cancel schedule (SCHEDULED → CANCELLED)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{scheduleId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "status": "CANCELLED",
    "cancelReason": "Member requested cancellation"
}

### 11. Mark as no-show (SCHEDULED → NO_SHOW)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/{{scheduleId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "status": "NOSHOW"
}